n{equation}\label{continuant} q_{n+k} \le (q_{n+1}+q_n) q_{n,k} \le q_n q_{n,k} \left(  rac{q_{n+1}}{q_n}+1ight) \le q_n q_{n,k} \cdot \left( rac{1}{f_n \left(1-\left( rac{f_n}{q_n}ight)^2ight)}+1ight), \end{equation} by (ef{c22}). Taking into account the first inequality from (ef{c31}) and monotonicity of $f(x)$, finally we obtain $$ \delta_n\ge  rac{f\left(A_n q_n^2\cdot \left( rac{1}{f_n \left(1-\left( rac{f_n}{q_n}ight)^2ight)}+1ight) ight) }{(A_nq_n)^2} \cdot \left( 1- rac{2f_{n+k}}{ q_{n,k}^2} ight)> (1-\varepsilon)  rac{f\left( rac{A_n q_n^2}{f_n}+2 ight) }{(A_nq_n)^2}, $$ for $n $ large enough. As $\alpha_{n+1}+\alpha_n^* > rac{1}{f_n}+\delta_n$ by (ef{perron}) we conclude that for any $\varepsilon>0$ for large $n$ under our consideration we have $$ \left|\alpha -  rac{p_n}{q_n}ight| <  rac{f_n}{q_n^2} \left( 1- (1-\varepsilon)  rac{ f_n \cdot f\left( rac{A_n q_n^2}{f_n}+2 ight) }{(A_nq_n)^2}ight). $$ Theorem 2 is proven.$\Box$ \vskip+0.3cm { f Acknowledgements} \,\, Sergei Pitcyn's research is supported by Russian Scientific Foundation, grant no.~25-11-00112, https://rscf.ru/project/25-11-00112/. Nikolay Moshchevitin’s research is supported by Austrian Science Fund (FWF), Forschungsprojekt PAT1961524.  egin{thebibliography}{10}  ibitem{cas} {\it J. Cassels,} { An Introduction to Diophantine Approximation,} Cambridge Tracts in Mathematics and Mathematical Physics, Vol. 45, Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, 1957.  ibitem{Cus} {\it T. Cusick; M. Flahive,} The Markoff and Lagrange spectra, Math. Surveys Monogr., vol. 30, Amer. Math. Soc., Providence, RI (1989).  ibitem{H} {\it J. Han\v{c}l}, On a Theorem of A. A. Markoff, Results in Mathematics, 76, article number 192, (2021).  ibitem{KM} {\it I.D. Kan; N.G. Moshchevitin,} Approximations to two real numbers. Unif. Distrib. Theory 5:2 (2010), 79–86.  ibitem{M} {\it N. Moshchevitin,} Über die Funktionen des Irrationalitätsmaßes für zwei irrationale Zahlen, Arch. Math. { f 112}:2 (2019), 161--